<body> 

  <h1>🌈 Book Store Project – Session 2</h1> 

  <div class="box"> 
    <h2>🎯 Purpose</h2> 
    <p>In this session, students will <b>decorate their Book Store page</b> using more HTML and CSS features.  
    They’ll learn to add background colors, lists, and links to make their webpage fun and colorful!</p> 
  </div> 

  <div class="box"> 
    <h2>🧩 What Students Will Learn</h2> 
    <ul> 
      <li>✅ Use of <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> for lists</li> 
      <li>✅ How to create links using <code>&lt;a&gt;</code></li> 
      <li>✅ Add background colors and borders with CSS</li> 
      <li>✅ Use <code>:hover</code> to change link styles</li> 
    </ul> 
  </div> 

  <div class="box"> 
    <h2>💻 Example HTML Code</h2> 
    <pre><code>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" /&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;

  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1 class="title"&gt;📚 Book Store&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p class="author"&gt;Author: Kareem Ashraf&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;He loves writing about ancient Egyptian culture and history.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;h2&gt;📖 My Favorite Genres&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;History&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Adventure&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Science&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;Learn more about the author: 
      &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt" target="_blank"&gt;Click Here&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;img src="https://images-eu.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/71LPCoF-MAL._AC_UL210_SR210,210_.jpg" width="200"&gt;
    &lt;img src="https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1444690560i/26889785.jpg" width="150"&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
    </code></pre> 
  </div> 

  <div class="box"> 
    <h2>🎨 Example CSS Code (styles.css)</h2> 
    <pre><code>
body {
  background-color: #fff8e7;
  font-family: "Comic Sans MS", sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
}

.title {
  color: #0077cc;
  border-bottom: 3px solid #0077cc;
  padding-bottom: 10px;
}

.author {
  color: darkred;
  font-weight: bold;
}

ul {
  list-style-type: square;
  color: #008000;
  text-align: left;
  display: inline-block;
}

a {
  color: #ff6600;
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}
    </code></pre> 
  </div> 

  <div class="box"> 
    <h2>📸 Example Result</h2> 
    <div class="example-img"> 
